  "notes": "Javanese in Latin script. DH = retroflex /ɖ/, TH = retroflex /ʈ/ (from Sanskrit influence). Word-final K → /ʔ/ in many varieties. Unaccented 'a' = /ɔ/ (Central Javanese). 'e' without accent = schwa /ə/; é = /e/; è = /ɛ/. Prenasalized stops (mb, nd, nj, ng) are single phonemes.",
